# Tailwind CSS & shadcn/ui Integration

## Current Setup
- Tailwind CSS v4 is installed
- PostCSS configuration is in place via [postcss.config.mjs](mdc:postcss.config.mjs)

## Integration Guidelines
1. **CSS Variables**: shadcn/ui uses CSS variables for theming in [globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css)
2. **Configuration**: Tailwind config will be updated during shadcn/ui init
3. **Class Merging**: Use `cn()` utility for conditional classes (provided by shadcn/ui)

## After shadcn/ui Initialization
- CSS variables for colors will be added to globals.css
- Tailwind config will include shadcn/ui plugin and configuration
- Component styles will follow shadcn/ui patterns

## Best Practices
- Use Tailwind utilities for layout and spacing
- Use shadcn/ui components for interactive elements
- Leverage CSS variables for consistent theming
- Use `cn()` for conditional styling in components

## Example Usage
```typescript
import { cn } from "@/lib/utils"

// Conditional styling with cn()
<Button className={cn("w-full", isLoading && "opacity-50")} />
```